snippet: The measure, which passed by an overwhelming margin one day before Sunday’s deadline, is remarkably similar to the one Greek voters rejected less than a week ago.
abstract: Greek Parliament approves Prime Min Alexis Tsipras's plan for three-year, $59 billion rescue package with stringent austerity terms; analysts say European creditors will still be skeptical that Greece's fractured government will be capable of adhering to difficult economic action.

byline.original: By LIZ ALDERMAN and ANDREW HIGGINS
byline.contributor: Liz Alderman reported from Athens, and Andrew Higgins from Brussels. Reporting was contributed by James Kanter from Brussels; Niki Kitsantonis, Suzanne Daley, Anemona Hartocollis and Dimitris Bounias from Athens; Alison Smale from Berlin; and Rick Lyman from Warsaw.

lead_paragraph: The measure, which passed by an overwhelming margin one day before Sunday’s deadline, is remarkably similar to the one Greek voters rejected less than a week ago.

headline.main: Greece’s Parliament Approves Prime Minister’s Bailout Plan
headline.print_headline: Greece’s Parliament Approves Prime Minister’s Bailout Plan
